              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Mono-energetic neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Periodic irradiations of the samples in a",
                "well-defined neutron flux followed by the measurement",
                "of the time dependence of delayed neutron activity.",
                "Two different types of experiments:",
                "- measurements of the delayed neutron abundances and",
                "periods,",
                "- measurements of the total delayed neutron yields.",
                "The irradiation time intervals were 15, 180 and 300 s.",
                "Depending on background conditions the delayed neutron",
                "counting intervals were 424.5 and 724.5 s with the time",
                "channel sequence after the end of sample irradiation:",
                " 0.01 s (150 channels), 0.02 s (150 channels), 0.1 s",
                " (200 channels), 1 s (200 channels) and 10 s (30 or",
                " 50 channels)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "D4PI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For delayed neutron registration, thirty SNM-11",
                " boron counters assembly in polyethylene cylinder of",
                " 400 mm diameter and 300 mm length.Counters were placed",
                " at three circles of 106, 160, 110 mm diameters.",
                " In the center - hole of 36mm diameter to sample flight",
                " tube. Boron carbide powder, borated polyethylene,",
                " cadmium sheets - for detector protection.",
                "The neutron detector dead time measured with a 252Cf",
                "spontaneous fission neutron source is 2.3+-0.2 micros.",
                "Stability of neutron detector parameters and",
                "appropriate electronic modules was controlled with the",
                "help of isotopic neutron sources - Am(Li) and Pu(Li).",
                "Neutron detector placed at 3 m aside from accelerator",
                "target."
              ]
            }
          ],
